<paragraph blockId="17.[810,1452,1814,2092]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[810,932,1814,1840]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The group 
<taxonomicName box="[1099,1171,1814,1840]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apalai">
<emphasis box="[1099,1171,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">apalai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the following combination of characters: Medium total length; PA pronounced, continuous to PI; two embolar keels, PAc absent; prolateral embolus without serrated area, represented by few (two–four) cusps distal to PAc.
</paragraph>
